"{\"uid\": \"m.economictimes.com-news-defence-kremlin-suggests-ukraine-would-use-an-olympic-truce-to-try-to-regroup-articleshow-109344343.cms\", \"text\": \"The Kremlin responded cautiously to French President Macron's proposal for an Olympic truce during the Paris Games, expressing concerns that Ukraine might exploit the pause to regroup and rearm. While suspending conflicts during the Olympics is a tradition, Kremlin spokesperson Dmitry Peskov noted Ukraine's past behavior during such pauses. However, he stopped short of ruling out the truce, stating no official steps had been taken. Macron expressed determination to pursue a truce in Ukraine, Gaza, and Sudan, intending to engage Chinese President Xi Jinping on the matter.    (Catch all theBusiness News,Breaking NewsandLatest NewsUpdates onThe Economic Times.)  Subscribe toThe Economic Times Primeand read theET ePaperonline.  (Catch all theBusiness News,Breaking NewsandLatest NewsUpdates onThe Economic Times.)  Subscribe toThe Economic Times Primeand read theET ePaperonline.    Groww = Angel One+ IIFL Capital + Nuvama. Should you bid?  India's IPO market is sizzling hot, but the message is worrisome  Banks have fixed the NPA crisis, but a new problem rears its head  Is pre-open trading a waste of time?  Air India wanted to create an IndiGo rival, instead it landed in an INR6k crore mess  Stock picks of the week: 5 stocks with consistent score improvement and return potential of more than 26% in 1 year  NALSA@30: PM stresses 'justice in people's language' at Supreme Court event  Is Tej Pratap-Ravi Kishan's second 'Coincidental' meeting a clue?  Trump backs Indian-origin Vivek Ramaswamy for Ohio Governor 2026  Priyanka vs Rajnath on '\\u20b910000 bribe', 'Musalman Matlab ..'  Politics over SIR in Bengal: BJP alleges infiltration, CPI(M) reacts  Physics Wallah set for stock market debut  'Katta aur Rangdaar': Modi in Bihar blasts RJD  India gets 4 new Vande Bharat Express trains : Key details here  Explained: Elon Mu